<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PaLTM2.7.10">
<l>ceṇpaka mallikai yōṭu ceṅkaḻu nīriru vāṭci</l>
<l>yeṇpakar pūvum koṇarntē ṉiṉṟivai cūṭṭavā veṉṟu</l>
<l>maṇpakar koṇṭāṉai yāycci makiḻnturai ceytavim mālai</l>
<l>paṇpakar villiput tūrkkōṉ paṭṭar pirāṉcoṉṉa pattē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>This garland of ten [verses] were spoken by Paṭṭarpirāṉ,</l>
<l>king of Villiputtūr where melodies are uttered,</l>
<l>made of the joyful words of the herdess</l>
<l>about him who took and moved the earth saying,</l>
<l>“Come, so that [I can] adorn [you] with these today.</l>
<l>I’ve brought a number of blossoms,</l>
<l>such as the red water lily and Tuscan jasmine,</l>
<l>along with the Champaka and Himalayan jasmine”.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
